snp2.14:2.12:
“A bhikkhu should not wander at the wrong time;
but at the proper time he should walk to the village for alms.
For ties stick to one given to untimely wandering;
hence the buddhas do not wander at the wrong time. (11)

snp2.14:2.26:
“One should not kill living beings or take what is not given;
one should not speak falsely or drink intoxicants.
One should abstain from sex, from impure conduct;
one should not eat at night [and] outside the prescribed time. (25)
